## Current Facts To Use

- Project name: SchemeSeva.
- Tagline: Find government schemes you may likely qualify for - and get alerted when new matches appear.
- Live demo: https://scheme-seva-agent.vercel.app/
- GitHub repository: https://github.com/YellankiKaushik/Scheme-Seva-Agent
- Current catalog: 28 verified Central + Telangana schemes.
- Main app route: `/app`.
- Scheme catalog route: `/schemes`.
- Architecture route: `/architecture`.
- Integration diagnostics route: `/debug/integrations`.
- Mandatory stack: Mastra-style workflow adapter, Qdrant retrieval/memory, and Enkrypt AI validation.
- Supporting stack: OpenRouter, Gemini embeddings, Langfuse, Upstash Redis, Vercel, TanStack Start, Vite, Nitro, React, and TypeScript.
- Supabase is optional fallback only.
- Reports use likely eligibility wording and are guidance only.
- Final eligibility and application steps must be confirmed on official portals.
- The app does not collect Aadhaar numbers or bank account numbers.
- The app does not automatically submit applications.

Use the final docs listed above for any public, judging, or developer-facing description of the project.
